@cheesetrader1 @emilyehman @Huskervball @BadgerVB One person's fun is another person's roller coaster nightmare, one in which I am caught up in three hours of cycling between faint glimmers of hope and abject despair.  To paraphrase "Airplane," I picked the wrong week to give up tranquilizers.

@AreaRED Having to play the late game in Nebraska, which may well go five sets, travel for three hours in the middle of the night, lose an hour in the time change, and then try to sleep to recover for what may be another five set match in the early game on Saturday is pretty unreasonable.

@AreaRED But OSU does play the Gophers in the early game on Friday so they do have to play what should be a tough match before they face us, although both are at home. It is a rare weekend that I will be rooting for the Golden Rats (although not in football).
@AreaRED Because the B1G wanted to make it as hard as possible for the Badgers to win the conference for the fourth time in a row.

@cheesetrader1 @emilyehman You're probably right if we are predicting the outcome.  Everyone loves the scrappy underdog story (I do too) so Wisconsin's sustained success is a negative.  I just don't think the Wisconsin coaching staff gets enough credit for what has been an amazing season.

@cheesetrader1 @emilyehman I have no doubt that KSC is and will continue to be a great coach.  But PSU is 11-7 in the B1G.  I just don't think that compares to 17-1 with all of the challenges the Badgers have overcome.  The 2022 team has the same number of B1G wins as the NC team with two more games to go.
@cheesetrader1 @emilyehman Sustaining that level of success when you have great players is one thing but doing it with a really young team and a different system is entirely on a different level.

@cheesetrader1 @emilyehman Yet, here the Badgers are at 17-1 in the B1G, #3 in the AVCA poll, most ranked wins in the country, and knocking on the door of their fourth conference championship in a row.  How does Kelly Sheffield not get COTY in the B1G?  I just don't get it.

@cheesetrader1 @emilyehman This year, we have a new system with the 6-2, two first-time setters, a first-year libero and two transfers (Franklin and Crawford) that had to be integrated into the system.  Emily did not have a single Badger player in the top-10 of her pre-season list. . . .

@cheesetrader1 @emilyehman I honestly am confused and maybe you can help me understand your COTY preferences.  Wisconsin lost two multi-year first-team AAs (Rettke and Hilley), two other players with AA recognition (Loberg and Barnes), and a cornerstone of their defense (Civita). . . .
